				<td colspan="2"><span>Hello all, this is my first post on this uber website <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /> So heres the deal, my little bard twinky is raising in lvls fast and its time for me to start banking higher lvl weps, which brings me to my question....whats a better piercer for bards 
<br />

<br />
Etched Bone Spike
<br />
LORE ITEM MAGIC ITEM  
<br />
Weight: 2.2 Size: SMALL 
<br />
Slot: PRIMARY SECONDARY  
<br />
Damage: 14 Delay: 23 
<br />
Ratio: 1.642 Amazing 
<br />
Str: +15 Dex: +8 Sta: +10 HP: +65 Mana: +30  
<br />
Brass Instruments: 18
<br />
Attack +5
<br />
Rec. lvl 58
<br />

<br />
OR
<br />

<br />
Battle Drummer's Main-Gauche   
<br />
LORE ITEM MAGIC ITEM  
<br />
Weight: 1.2 Size: SMALL 
<br />
Slot: PRIMARY SECONDARY  
<br />
Damage: 11 Delay: 17 
<br />
Dex: +5 Sta: +5 Cha: +5 Magic Resist: +8 Mana: +40 
<br />
Percussion: 20
<br />
Rec. lvl 56
<br />

<br />
Some of you might think this is a dumb question considering the etched bone spike has way better stats, but what I am hung up on is that I already have a troubadors mace so I have the brass mod covered.  So, what im wondering is, does it make sense to have two weps with the same mod ? Or should I ditch the mace all together and wield these two piercers ?  Maybe my question shoulda been &quot;What is the best droppable weapon combo for bards.&quot;  I am very anal when it comes to EQ and I like to try and keep characters as best equipped as possible, so any help you guys can offer me would be greatly appreciated.  Thanx all very much<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
Tarix </span></td>
