				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">
<br />
a fast 11/17 in primary mean more swings/duel wield checks....
<br />
</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
Just to mention something that I think needs to be mentioned...
<br />

<br />

<br />
DW has NOTHING to do with whats in your primary.
<br />

<br />
the DW check is done when the secondary refreshes, not when the primary attacks (bards can see this all the time just by equiping a primary inst.  You still attack with your secondary even though you are not attacking at all with the primary)
<br />

<br />
Another easy test is to get a really slow primary and a really fast secondary if another type..
<br />

<br />
for example with:
<br />
primary: 10/38 blunt
<br />
secondary: 7/18 piercing
<br />

<br />
sometimes you will attack twice with the secondary before the primary attacks again.
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
