				<td colspan="2"><span>In terms of raw melee DPS, the BDMG is significantly higher DPS than the etched bone spike -- especially in main hand.  Seriously, by ANY calculation, it is way better damage output.  Allakhazam efficiency rating, which is a measure of raw DPS potential with no stats or procs taken into account, puts the Spike at 89, the BDMG at 102.  Big difference.
<br />

<br />
Having said that, these are dual-use instrument/weapons and you simply need to decide whether or not you need the instrument mod of one over the other, or both.  If you really really need brass more, and can only equip one, then equip the spike.  What our songs do matters more than melee damage anyway.  But the simple fact is, there is almost no situation I can conceive of where you would prefer brass over percussion and if you can wield both, then it is very very simple -- BDMG in main, spike in secondary.</span></td>
