				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Etched Bone Spike vs. Battle Drummer's Main-Gauche<a name="33126"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 6 04 8:09 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>While it's true that a raw ratio comparison isn't the best way to choose your weapon, it's a pretty good place to start....
<br />

<br />
Consider the raw ratio's again:
<br />

<br />
11dmg/delay17 = 0.647 dmg per delay BDMG 
<br />
14dmg/23delay = 0.608 dmg per delay EBS 
<br />
13dmg/21delay = 0.619 dmg per delay on troubadour mace 
<br />

<br />
The highest ratio weapon there is the BDMG, which is also the fastest.  The second highest weapon ratio is the Troubador's Mace, which is also the second-fastest.
<br />

<br />
For raw weapon DPS, I would suggest BDMG main/Troub offhand.  
<br />

<br />
This also has the pleasent side effect of giving yourself two innate mods from your weapons (percussion/brass), as opposed to having a set of weapons that carry the same modifier (1.8 brass mod on both).
<br />

<br />
Granted, we aren't a class that churns out a ton of melee DPS, but I still use the same general rules that I used to use for my ranger.  Pick weapons based on their damage output or other &quot;utility&quot; (hadda slip that in there -- things like the epic are irreplaceable until a lot lot lot later).  
<br />

<br />
In this scenario, you're getting the best of both worlds: more DPS by using the BDMG, *and* more utility (the percussion mod).  Things like stats are secondary when it comes to choosing weapons, unless it's something ungodly like 200 HP or something<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
However, the +5 atk might help you a bit, perhaps in the offhand?  It may come close to bridging the smaller gap between the troub mace, and you'll still have your brass mod covered.
<br />

<br />
Anyhow, the short answer to your question:  if it comes down to choosing which weapon to pair with your troub mace, go with the BDMG in my opinion...</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%">Veteran Lalados,
65 bard</span></td>
